# BeatSwipe — Core Rules

Producer swipe portfolio for Instagram bio links. Fans swipe beats, save Favorites, buy via producer store links. BeatSwipe takes no cut. Luca = PO, deployer, user #1.

**More detail:** `@beatswipe-archive.mdc` (history, code maps, long changelogs — only when needed).

## Marketing

- **Never** say „Tinder" (brand)
- Slogan: „Discover Beats. Save What Hits."
- Product: „Your swipe page for the bio" / „Free swipe portfolio for producers"

## Product (Phase 1)

- **Core:** `beatswipe.app/p/producername` — full-screen swipe portfolio (not a beat list profile)
- **Home:** Landing + tool marketing; Discover/Favorites exist but invite-gated
- **Onboarding:** Invite code from Luca (DM) — gated: Discover, Favorites, My Page, Profile. Open: Landing, `/p/*`
- **Monetization:** none now (student). No cut on beat sales.
- **Mobile-first** (Instagram traffic). `/p/` keeps beat glow, not app purple wash.

## Code layout

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `index.html` | HTML + small init block |
| `app.js` | Discover, auth, favorites, profile, nav, swipe, toast |
| `mypage.js` | My Page upload, dashboard, beat edit/order |
| `portfolio.js` | `/p/` portfolio |
| `styles.css` | All CSS |
| `api/*.js` | beats, pending-beats, manage-beat, submit-beat, crate |

**Script order:** `/app.js` → `/mypage.js` → `/portfolio.js` → init inline in `index.html`

**Asset paths:** always root-absolute (`/styles.css`, `/app.js`, …) — relative breaks on `/p/slug` rewrites.

**No duplicate functions** across html/js modules.

